__pycache__/
*.pyc
.DS_Store
result
result-*

# vendor/ is a local staging area only, never part of the git repo -- see
# vendor/README.md. Every manual-local package (grandMA3 onPC, Blackmagic
# Desktop Video/ATEM Software Control, Dante Virtual Soundcard, Spotify)
# turned out to be a multi-hundred-MB (or multi-GB) installer, way past
# GitHub's 100MB push limit and past what Git LFS's free tier can hold
# comfortably -- so none of it gets committed, ever. Installers get placed
# by hand (or via `scripts/update_packages.py provision` / `nix run
# .#provision-vendor`) at the fixed absolute paths named in packages.json's
# "localPath" fields instead (e.g. /Users/Shared/nc-vendor/<name>), which
# live outside this directory entirely.
vendor/*
!vendor/README.md
